Date: Fri 15 Jul 2022
Source: WOAH-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/report-info?reportId=57095


Lumpy skin disease virus (inf. with), Cambodia
-----------------------------------------------------
Follow-up report [FUR] no. 23

Started: 26 May 2021
Confirmed: 4 Jun 2021
The event is ongoing.

Quantitative data summary
Measuring unit: animal
Species / Type / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered / Vaccinated
Cattle / new / 189 / 18 / 1 / 0 / 0 / -
Cattle / total* / 12 017 / 1672 / 37 / 0 / 0 / -
Buffaloes / new / - / - / - / - / - / -
Buffaloes / total / 20 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / -
All species / new / 189 / 18 / 1 / 0 / 0 / -
All species / total / 12 037 / 1672 / 37 / 0 / 0 / -
[*Total = May 2021 - Jul 2022]

New outbreaks (2)
1. Location: Tmey village, Brosat commune, Kiri Vong district, Takeo [Takev] province
Started: 28 May 2022
Description of the affected population: LSD affected a smallholder cattle farm in the village.
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered / Vaccinated
Cattle / 128 / 15 / 1 / 0 / 0 / -

2. Location: Tropeang Chhouk village, Tro Lach commune, Treang district, Takeo province
Started: 6 Jun 2022
Description of the affected population: LSD affected smallholder cattle farms in the village.
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered / Vaccinated
Cattle / 150 / 12 / 2 / 0 / 0 / -

All species total / 150 / 12 / 2 / 0 / 0 / -

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the WOAH report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[In addition to the 2 new LSD outbreaks in the province of Takeo addressed in the above WAHIS FUR, a 3rd new outbreak has been identified in the Koh Kokkor village, Kaoh Tontuem Commune, Kampong Siem district, Kampong Cham province. It was initially observed on 30 Jun 2022 and reported, after being confirmed, on 13 Jul 2022. See, with map, at https://empres-i.apps.fao.org/event-report/326928.

The total number of LSD outbreaks in Cambodia, including the 3 new outbreaks addressed in this posting, is now 59. - Mod.AS]
